      "parameters": {
        "text": "={{ $json.Content }}",
        "attributes": {
          "attributes": [
            {
              "name": "tp_status",
              "description": "=Extract the CURRENT trade outcome status.\n\nReturn ONLY one of the following values:\n- TPxx        (e.g. TP1, TP2, TP7)\n- SL\n- BREAKEVEN\n- null\n\nRules:\n- Return SL if the text contains an explicit loss indication such as:\n  - \"SL\"\n  - \"Stop loss\"\n  - \"Stopped out\"\n  - A negative R:R value (e.g. \"-1R\", \"-4R\") clearly associated with the trade\n- SL does NOT require verbs like \"hit\" or \"stopped\" if SL or a negative R:R is explicitly stated.\n- Return TPx only if a take-profit level is confirmed or reasonably inferred.\n- Return BREAKEVEN if stop-loss is moved to breakeven (e.g. \"SL to BE\").\n- Ignore target price lists, entry details, leverage, and risk management text.\n- If multiple outcomes appear, prioritize in order: SL > BREAKEVEN > TPx.\n- If no outcome can be inferred, return \"NO\".",
              "required": true
            },
            {
              "name": "rr_value",
              "description": "=Extract the Risk-to-Reward (R:R) value related to the CURRENT trade outcome.\n\nReturn the value ONLY in one of the following formats:\n- +xR\n- -xR\n\nWhere x can be an integer or decimal number.\n\nRules:\n- Positive R:R (+xR) is valid ONLY if it is associated with a CONFIRMED or INFERRED TP hit.\n- Negative R:R (-xR) is valid if it is associated with a CONFIRMED or INFERRED stop-loss or loss event.\n- If TP and R:R appear together in an ambiguous or messy format (e.g. \"TP73+4R\"), extract the R:R value and allow later inference.\n- Ignore R:R values that clearly belong to entry, leverage, or tar\n- If no outcome can be inferred, return \"NO\"",
              "required": true
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
